176
00:09:19,434 --> 00:09:21,770
<font face="Serif" size="18">If I were you, I'd be mad about that.</font>

177
00:09:21,853 --> 00:09:24,647
<font face="Serif" size="18">You are me. And why would I be mad at myself?</font>

178
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:27,400
<font face="Serif" size="18">Good point. ls there anything to eat?</font>

179
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:29,986
<font face="Serif" size="18">- There's a kitchenette.
- Oh, a kitchenette.</font>

180
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,072
<font face="Serif" size="18">- Such red carpet treatment.
- Excuse me?</font>

181
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:35,075
<font face="Serif" size="18">Thank you, I love it. We're all part of Morty.</font>

182
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,535
<font face="Serif" size="18">Some of us more important parts than others...</font>

183
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:40,121
<font face="Serif" size="18">The part of me that's my father is a twat.</font>

184
00:09:40,205 --> 00:09:42,415
<font face="Serif" size="18">That's also gonna be funny when we get back.</font>

185
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:44,626
<font face="Serif" size="18">Next time you try to do a <i>Die Hard,</i></font>

186
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:48,338
<font face="Serif" size="18">don't hide under a long table
like the guy from <i>Die Hard.</i></font>

187
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:50,590
<font face="Serif" size="18">- [screams]
- Okay, I won't.</font>

188
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,927
<font face="Serif" size="18">You said she doesn't know <i>Die Hard.</i></font>

189
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:56,513
<font face="Serif" size="18">- She doesn't.
- She's killing us off one by one.</font>

190
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:59,682
<font face="Serif" size="18">What do you expect her to do,
buy us each an ice cream, two by two?</font>

191
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:03,436
<font face="Serif" size="18">She's improvising,
which is how she's going to fall into our trap.</font>

192
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,313
<font face="Serif" size="18">I'm going to wander the arcade unarmed,</font>

193
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:07,982
<font face="Serif" size="18">and when she comes across me,
I'll pretend to be a hostage.</font>

194
00:10:08,066 --> 00:10:09,818
<font face="Serif" size="18">And because she hasn't seen <i>Die Hard,</i></font>

195
00:10:09,901 --> 00:10:13,530
<font face="Serif" size="18">instead of handing me an unloaded gun,
she'll hand me a--</font>

196
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,740
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>Die Hard! Die Hard! Die Hard!</i></font>

197
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:19,369
<font face="Serif" size="18">- What the hell was that?
- [Summer] Die Hard! Die Hard!</font>

198
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:22,997
<font face="Serif" size="18">You can't keep yelling <i>"Die Hard"
</i></font><font face="Serif" size="18">into a walkie-talkie and--</font>

199
00:10:23,081 --> 00:10:25,166
<font face="Serif" size="18">She threw her walkie-talkie away.</font>

200
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:27,085
<font face="Serif" size="18">She hates <i>Die Hard.</i></font>

201
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:31,005
<font face="Serif" size="18">Which makes her the ultimate McClane.</font>

202
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:35,260
<font face="Serif" size="18">Forget everything you know about <i>Die Hard
</i></font><font face="Serif" size="18">and just go shoot that bitch.</font>

203
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:37,846
<font face="Serif" size="18">[president]
Thank you for meeting with me, Mr. Roy.</font>

204
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:41,182
<font face="Serif" size="18">Half the country hangs on your word.
Heck, most of them.</font>

205
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:43,268
<font face="Serif" size="18">You're like a pope, I reckon.</font>

206
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:46,354
<font face="Serif" size="18">I'm not. It's not a religion.
We're in a video game.</font>

207
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:48,648
<font face="Serif" size="18">I've heard the message.
You're not on the clock here.</font>

208
00:10:48,731 --> 00:10:51,985
<font face="Serif" size="18">You want every single person on a spaceship,
but you got a bunch of holdouts.</font>

209
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:54,654
<font face="Serif" size="18">Maybe people that prefer
their leaders a little more elected.</font>

210
00:10:54,737 --> 00:10:58,575
<font face="Serif" size="18">Right. Your voters. People that like
being told what to do but don't like admitting it.</font>

211
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:01,161
<font face="Serif" size="18">- Not sure I'd put it that way.
- You'd put it a stupid way.</font>

212
00:11:01,244 --> 00:11:04,956
<font face="Serif" size="18">This was a waste of time.
I've got 92% of you ready to vamoose.</font>

213
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:07,709
<font face="Serif" size="18">We're not gonna get the rest
by making deals with parasites.</font>

214
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:12,088
<font face="Serif" size="18">Mr. President, Roy is Rick. He's not us.
You and I, we're Morty.</font>

215
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:13,381
<font face="Serif" size="18">Is that so hard to believe?</font>

216
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:15,800
<font face="Serif" size="18">I've known it and believed it longer.</font>

217
00:11:15,884 --> 00:11:18,011
<font face="Serif" size="18">We became video-game characters
at the same moment,</font>

218
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:21,931
<font face="Serif" size="18">but I knew the truth before you dropped
your skateboard and went to your first cult meeting.</font>

219
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,434
<font face="Serif" size="18">How do you think a guy
becomes a president, honey?</font>

220
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:25,852
<font face="Serif" size="18">By not paying attention?</font>

221
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:28,646
<font face="Serif" size="18">Sorry to call you honey,
I know we're parts of a 14-year-old boy,</font>

222
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:31,107
<font face="Serif" size="18">but my part's old-fashioned
and vaguely Southern.</font>

223
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:33,902
<font face="Serif" size="18">I'm confused. if you know Rick is real, why--?</font>

224
00:11:33,985 --> 00:11:36,529
<font face="Serif" size="18">Why hold out?
Because he's a rude, entitled cock.</font>

225
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:39,532
<font face="Serif" size="18">He's here to save us. He could've let us die.</font>

226
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:40,742
<font face="Serif" size="18">He spent 50 years--</font>

227
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:43,244
<font face="Serif" size="18">Fifty years, it's what, a couple hours to him?</font>

228
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:46,623
<font face="Serif" size="18">He refuses to leave without his grandson,
but what's "grandson" mean to him?</font>

229
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:47,957
<font face="Serif" size="18">Sounds like it means butler.</font>

230
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:51,169
<font face="Serif" size="18">Someone to "Help Summer
with her <i>Die Hard,"</i></font><font face="Serif" size="18"> whatever that means.</font>

231
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:53,880
<font face="Serif" size="18">I'll tell you what it doesn't mean.
Fly fishing. A hug.</font>

232
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:57,050
<font face="Serif" size="18">A little appreciation for what
is clearly a pretty decent kid.</font>

233
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,552
<font face="Serif" size="18">At least the 8% of him
that makes up the decent half</font>

234
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:01,679
<font face="Serif" size="18">of the greatest goddamn nation on the planet.</font>

235
00:12:01,763 --> 00:12:05,016
<font face="Serif" size="18">We're not a person to him yet.
We're not Morty yet. We're divided.</font>

236
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:07,435
<font face="Serif" size="18">We're divided
because some of us don't trust the guy.</font>

237
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:09,854
<font face="Serif" size="18">What happens when we're all back together?</font>

238
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:13,191
<font face="Serif" size="18">One Morty? indivisible?
Under a cranky old bag of dicks?</font>

239
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:16,986
<font face="Serif" size="18">A man you can lock in a box with five billion pieces
of his own goddamn flesh and blood</font>

240
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:20,573
<font face="Serif" size="18">for 50 goddamn simulated years
and never hear him say "I love you"?</font>

241
00:12:21,324 --> 00:12:23,868
<font face="Serif" size="18">Sorry, pumpkin tits, that dog don't hunt.</font>

242
00:12:25,036 --> 00:12:28,456
<font face="Serif" size="18">Want some heroin?
It's a video game, might as well.</font>

243
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:33,044
<font face="Serif" size="18">Just about ready for launch.</font>

244
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:36,047
<font face="Serif" size="18">I can get out of these clothes.
I don't have nearly enough pockets.</font>

245
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:38,091
<font face="Serif" size="18">It'll be nice to have my own dick back.</font>

246
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:41,803
<font face="Serif" size="18">- You're fine leaving 8% of me to die?
- It's not your finest 8%\, Morty.</font>

247
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,846
<font face="Serif" size="18">And 8%\ of anything is expendable.</font>

248
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:45,431
<font face="Serif" size="18">Eight percent of pizza is crust.</font>

249
00:12:45,515 --> 00:12:47,892
<font face="Serif" size="18">Eight percent of the Snyder Cut
was Batman dreaming.</font>

250
00:12:47,976 --> 00:12:50,478
<font face="Serif" size="18">I don't know that reference.
We're in a video game.</font>

251
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:53,314
<font face="Serif" size="18">- Not for long, baby.
- I'm not leaving without all of me.</font>

252
00:12:53,398 --> 00:12:55,358
<font face="Serif" size="18">What? Let me crunch these numbers.</font>

253
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,986
<font face="Serif" size="18">Eight percent of five billion plus one person--</font>

254
00:12:58,069 --> 00:13:01,322
<font face="Serif" size="18">- If you stay, it changes nothing.
- <i>If she's not going,</i></font>

255
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:05,243
<font face="Serif" size="18">- <i>I don't think my country wants to go.
</i></font><font face="Serif" size="18">- Who invited you to chime in, monitor face?</font>

256
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:07,787
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>Why give me a monitor
if my opinion doesn't matter?</i></font>

257
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:10,790
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>Your opinion isn't allowed to matter.
We're all Morty.</i></font>

258
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:12,834
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>How many of us are we supposed to give up?</i></font>

259
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:16,129
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>Look, I don't know about you,
but I was already taking a big leap of faith.</i></font>

260
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:19,215
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>We're basically giving up our lives
to become a tiny part of a stranger.</i></font>

261
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:21,634
<font face="Serif" size="18">- <i>These lives aren't real.
- Yeah, but they're longer.</i></font>

262
00:13:21,718 --> 00:13:24,971
<font face="Serif" size="18">- [all shouting]
- What is this, suicide by summit meeting?</font>

263
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:25,930
<font face="Serif" size="18">Everyone stop!</font>

264
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:30,601
<font face="Serif" size="18">Rick, I'll get every single part
